@NEXT "MAIN"
@{par}
@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}MAGIC WORKBENCH STUFF 5.2
by
Trevor Morris@{apen 1}

@{"       Appology!       " LINK "Sorry"}

@{"     Introduction      " LINK "Intro"}
@{"  System Requirements  " LINK "Require"}
@{"     Installation      " LINK "Install"}
@{"  For your interest... " LINK "Interest"}
@{"        Author         " LINK "Author"}
@{"       History         " LINK "History"}

@{"       Thanks to...    " LINK "Thanks"}
@{"   This is CARDWARE!   " LINK "Card"}
@{"     Distribution      " LINK "Distribution"}
@{"      Disclaimer       " LINK "Disclaimer"}
@{"        Index          " LINK "Index"}

@{jleft}
@{body}@{b}NOTE@{ub}: This guide was designed using the features of MultiView V40+. Therefore,
those of you @{i}not@{ui} using OS3.1+ may not get all of the @{bpen 7}B@{bpen 0}e@{b}@{apen 8}n@{apen 9}@{ub}E@{bpen 11}@{apen 15}f@{bpen 0}@{apen 11}i@{bpen 13}@{apen 12}T@{bpen 0}@{apen 14}@{b}s@{ub}@{apen 1}. Also, the guide
was designed for (and looks best with) Xen.font 8, so I have "forced" this font.
To enable your own font, simply remove line 3 of this guide (@FONT Xen.font 8).
@{par}
@{par}@{b}SYSOPS@{ub}: Please name this achive @{b}MWStuf52.lha@{ub} if you post it. Thanx in advance!

@ENDNODE
@REMARK
@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Sorry" "Sorry guys!"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}Sorry guys!
@{jleft}@{apen 1}
@{body}In my archive (MWB_Stuff_5.lha), I fixed up and included some of Torsten
Hiddessen's patterns from his MagicBG.lha archive. Having not kept his
documentation or name, I decided to use his patterns in my archive (see
@{"Win_Patterns (dir)" LINK "WP"}). I should not have done this and I appologize to him.
Torsten Hiddessen, being a reasonable chap that he is, however, has given me
permission to include them in this archive and I wish to thank him for it.
@{par}
@{par}I also made a mistake in the guide file, in which I stated that @{"MagicSelector" LINK "MS"} by
0yvind Falch, Triumph Software, was @{i}now ShareWare@{ui}. Well, it has always
been ShareWare - what I meant to say was that it was now FREEWARE!
@{par}
@{par}@{b}AND@{ub} finally (hopefully), I also accidentally included MagicWB-Demon in my
MWB_Stuff_5 and 5.1 archives, which I did not realize is exclusively available
to registered users of @{"Magic Workbench 2.0 (© Martin Huttenloher)" LINK "MWB"}. Since I @{i}am@{ui} a
registered user, I've been using MagicWB-Demon for a long time and never really
thought about it when I included it. My sincere appologies Martin! For those of
you who are NOT registered users (get to it ;-) there are alternatives: Colorado
and ColorManager (both of which are available on aminet and mirrors). I am
currently using ColorManager and I think it is quite nice (comes with a Prefs
program and the whole deal).

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Intro" "Introduction"
@NEXT "Require"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}Introduction
@{jleft}@{apen 1}
@{body}MagicWBStuff is a collection of icons, patterns and other stuff which I make
for everyone to enjoy...all I ask is that you @{"send a postcard to Roman Patzner" LINK "Card"}
or @{"email me" LINK "Author"} to let me know what you think of this archive. All included icons
and patterns follow the MWB standards.
@{par}
@{par}The original archive should contain the following (as well, some files may
have associated icons):
@{par}@{code}
@{" C        (dir) " LINK "C"}
@{" Icons    (dir) " LINK "Icons"}
@{" Misc     (dir) " LINK "Misc"}
@{" MUI      (dir) " LINK "MUIDrawer"}
@{" P&C      (dir) " LINK "P&C"}
@{" Patterns (dir) " LINK "Patterns"}
@{" S        (dir) " LINK "S"}
@{" TrevsDB.iff    " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview TrevsDB.iff"}
@{" SYSOPS.README  " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview SYSOPS.README"}
@{b}Stuff5.2.guide@{ub} (you're reading it @{apen 2}@{b}:@{ub}@{apen 1})

@{b}NOTE TO SYSOPS:@{ub} If anything is missing/added from/to the above list, please
                delete the archive from your BBS (my intent is NOT to spread
                any viruses). Also, please read the @{"SYSOPS.README" SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview SYSOPS.README"}...Thanx!!

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "P&C" "Pointer & Color (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "Intro"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}Pointer & Color

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The P&C drawer should contain the following (as well, some files may have
associated icons):
@{par}@{code}
ClickForColors16 - Changes the palette to 16 colors (MWB).
ClickForColors8  - Changes the palette to 8 colors (MWB).
ClickForPointer  - Changes your pointer to look like mine.
ClickMeFirst     - Executes MagicWB-Demon (for correct 8 & 16 color palette).
                   (You need MagicWB-Demon for this to work - see @{"Sorry" LINK "Sorry"})
ClickMeForScreen - This will launch the ScreenPrefs util. If you want a 16 color
                   MWB, just slide the colors to 16; if you an 8 color MWB,
                   slide it to 8 colors and hit @{b}USE@{ub}.

@{body}This drawer contains my palette and pointer prefs. Double-Clicking on their
icons will only change your prefs until you reboot. If you wish to permanently
save these prefs, double-click on the icons and then load the appropriate prefs
util from your sys:prefs/ drawer (either PointerPrefs or PalettePrefs) and then
click on @{b}SAVE@{ub}. See @{"16_Color Icons" LINK "16"}.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "S" "S (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "Intro"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}S (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}The S drawer should contain the following:

Randomizer - a sample line for your startup-sequence (or user-startup)
             randomize your patterns using @{"FilePick by Simon Brown" LINK "FP"}.
Shell-Startup - my shell start-up (rename yours and try this one out).
AddMeToYourS-S - a sample line for 16 color MWB - See @{"16_Color Icons" LINK "16"}.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "MUIDrawer" "MUI (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "Intro"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}MUI (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The MUI/Images/Trevor/Gradient/8/ drawer should contain the
following images:
@{par}@{code}
ArrowDown.mf0     ArrowDown.mf1
ArrowLeft.mf0     ArrowLeft.mf1
ArrowRight.mf0    ArrowRight.mf1
ArrowUp.mf0       ArrowUp.mf1
CheckMark.mf0     CheckMark.mf1
Cycle.mbr         PopDrawer.mf0
PopDrawer.mf1     PopFile.mf0
PopFile.mf1       PopUp.mf0
PopUp.mf1         RadioButton.mf0
RadioButton.mf1

@{body}The CycleGad was copied from the included WD set, but I shortened it for
inclusion in my set.
@{par}
@{par}These are just some small images I drew for @{"MUI" LINK "MUI"} because I found that all the
other ones were to large. Copy them into your MUI drawer (The path follows the
@{"MUI3+" LINK "MUI"} convention - people using less than version 3 will have to alter the path
slightly).
@{par}
@{par}A Template is included in the @{"Misc (dir)" LINK "Misc"}.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Misc" "Misc (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "Intro"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}Misc (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The Misc drawer should contain the following (as well, some files may have
associated icons):
@{par}@{code}
@{" Courtney24.jpg " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview misc/Courtney24.jpg"}
@{" MUI_Template " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview misc/MUI_Template"}
@{" MWB_Template " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview misc/MWB_Template"}

@{body}The jpeg is a picture I painted from the cover of a People magazine (May 8,
1995) - I scanned the image and then painted out all of the text, logos and misc
images.  The image is provided here in two sizes. I then used this image in
conjunction with ADPro2.5 and DPaint to create the patterns in the
@{"Sml_Patterns (dir)" LINK "SP"}.
@{par}
@{par}The Templates may be used to create your own icons and buttons. They contain
all icon standards of which I am currently aware (let @{"me" LINK "Author"} know if you find any
that are missing).

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Patterns" "Patterns (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "Intro"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}Patterns (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The Patterns drawer should contain the following (as well, some files may have
associated icons):
@{par}@{code}
@{" Brushes      (dir) " LINK "Brushes"}
@{" Big_Patterns (dir) " LINK "BP"}
@{" Win_Patterns (dir) " LINK "WP"}
@{" Sml_Patterns (dir) " LINK "SP"}

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Brushes" "Brushes (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Patterns"
@TOC "Patterns"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}Brushes (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The Brushes drawer should contain the following:
@{par}
@{par}@{" Bart.brush " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/brushes/bart.brush"}
@{par}
@{par}The Bart.brush was saved under 640x400x3 (3 bitplane, 8 color, standard MWB
palette). You may use these to paste onto your favorite background. It is also
provided with a background in the @{"Sml_Patterns (dir)" LINK "SP"}.
@{par}
@{par}The Bart image was originally drawn by @{"Roman Patzner" LINK "Card"}, however, I
converted it to 8 colors and anti-aliased it (by hand!).

@ENDNODE


@NODE "WP" "Win_Patterns (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Patterns"
@TOC "Patterns"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}Win_Patterns (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The Win_Patterns drawer should contain the following:
@{par}@{code}
@{" ColoredStones.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/win_patterns/ColoredStones.iff"}
@{" FlagStone.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/win_patterns/FlagStone.iff"}
@{" Mush.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/win_patterns/Mush.iff"}
@{" Pebble.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/win_patterns/Pebble.iff"}
@{" Terrazzo.iff * " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/win_patterns/Terrazzo.iff"}
@{" ToiletPaper.iff * " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/win_patterns/ToiletPaper.iff"}
@{" WaterDrops.iff * " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/win_patterns/WaterDrops.iff"}
@{" Wood.iff * " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/win_patterns/Wood.iff"}

@{body}* These patterns are originally from @{"Torsten Hiddessen's MagicBG archive" LINK "Sorry"} on
Aminet (pix/mwb). I simply provided a consistant, standard MWB palette for each
image, and cleaned up some miscellanious pixels.
@{par}
@{par}Also, please note that if you recognise any others which may have been released
in other archives (like UselessMWB_Patterns), then they are included here
because I liked them enough to make them repeat. A lot of patterns which are
uploaded to aminet are non-repeating (and therefor annoying and useless), so I
spend a few minutes painting them up to repeat.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "SP" "Sml_Patterns (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Patterns"
@TOC "Patterns"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}Sml_Patterns (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The Sml_Patterns drawer should contain the following:
@{par}@{code}
@{" Bart.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/sml_patterns/Bart.iff"}
@{" Courtney2.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/sml_patterns/Courtney2.iff"}
@{" Courtney3.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/sml_patterns/Courtney3.iff"}
@{" Cute.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/sml_patterns/Cute.iff"}
@{" XFiles.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/sml_patterns/XFiles.iff"}
@{" XFiles2.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/sml_patterns/XFiles2.iff"}
@{" XFiles_MagicCopper.iff" SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/sml_patterns/XFiles_MagicCopper.iff"}

@{body}Bart, Courtney3 and XFiles and 3 bitplane (8 color), standard MWB palette
640x400 images, and Cute, Courtney2 and XFiles2 are only a 2 bitplane, 4 color
grey-scale images. The 8 color Courtney picture took me a HELL OF A LONG TIME
to draw, whereas the 4 color version was just rendered using ADPro2.5.
@{par}@{code}
            @{b}#      #
             #    #
              #  #@{ub}
 @{apen 3}The ®  F  I  L @{apen 1}@{b}#@{ub}@{apen 3} E  S@{apen 1}
               @{b}##
              #  #
             #    #
            #      #@{ub}

@{body}XFiles2 and XFiles_MagicCopper were originally drawn by Anders Bakkevold
(andersb@intercom.no). I used XFiles2 to create my own MWB pattern: XFiles. I
was asked by Anders Bakkevold to include the originals.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "BP" "Big_Patterns (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Patterns"
@TOC "Patterns"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}BIG_Patterns (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The Sml_Patterns drawer should contain the following:
@{par}@{code}
@{" Courtney2.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/big_patterns/Courtney2.iff"}
@{" Courtney4.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/big_patterns/Courtney4.iff"}
@{" KathyFlag.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/big_patterns/KathyFlag.iff"}
@{" MädchenAmick.iff " SYSTEM "sys:utilities/multiview patterns/big_patterns/MädchenAmick.iff"}

@{body}These are all 800x600, standard MWB palette images. Courtney4 and KathyFlag are
16 color images, and Courtney2 and MädchenAmick are 4 color (actually 3) images.
Courtney2 and MädchenAmick were rendered with ADPro2.5. See @{"For your interest.." LINK "Interest"}
to find out how to render your own grey-scale MWB images.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "Icons" "Icons (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
