@NODE "8" "8_Color (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Icons"
@TOC "Icons"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}8_Color (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}The 8_Color drawer should contain the following:

@{" Def_Icons    (dir) " LINK "DI"}
@{" Guides       (dir) " LINK "Guides"}
@{" ImageDrawers (dir) " LINK "ID"}
@{" Enlan        (dir) " LINK "Enlan"}

AMosaic.info         DiamondSfx.info
AMprefs.info         Fax.info
ANT.info             Hippo.info
Def_Asm.info         Install.info
Def_C.info           MEGABALL.info
Def_Cxx.info         NewDisk.info
Def_GST.info         PacMan.info
Def_H.info           Pooh.info
Def_Lst.info         SkidMarks.info
Def_Map.info         StopPicBoot.info
Def_Se.info          Tanks.info
Def_SMakeFile.info   The Settlers.info
Device.info          VChecker.info
DiamondGfx.info      ViewFax.info
DiamondPrefs.info

@{body}This drawer also contains a @{b}Settlers icon@{ub} and a @{b}MegaBall icon@{ub} done by my
little brother @{"Troy" LINK "Thanks"} (14 years old). In my opinion, I think it is better than some
of the other icons I have seen uploaded to Aminet by people who ask for
ShareWare fees!
@{par}
@{par}Please note that some icons are merely "fix-ups," others are converted to MWB
from other icon sets, and some are drawn from scratch. See @{"Thanks to..." LINK "Thanks"}. For
example, the Def_SasC icons were drawn by someone else on large brown
backgrounds, but I've just adapted them to a more standard MWB Icon.
@{par}
@{par}NewDisk.info was drawn by Steve Bridges in appreciation of MWB_Stuff_5! Thanx
Steve!

@ENDNODE


@NODE "DI" "Def_Icons (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "8"
@TOC "8"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}Def_Icons (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The Def_Icons drawer should contain the following icons:
@{par}@{code}
def_8SVX.info        def_anim.info
def_archive.info     def_basic.info
def_brush.info       def_c.info
def_CTLG.info        def_device.info
def_DOSDriver.info   def_DTYP.info
def_empty.info       def_filesystem.info
def_font.info        def_install.info
def_Keymap.info      def_library.info
def_Monitor.info     def_PREF.info
def_Printer.info     def_project.info
def_RADxdisk.info    def_tool.info

@{body}The ability to use these different default disk icons for different file
systems (so you can recognize the file system used by a disk by just looking
at its icon) is possible if you use @{b}DefIcons@{ub} which is part of the @{b}NewIcons@{ub} package.
When DefIcons is installed, icons matching a specific type will be assigned an
icon from your prefs:env-archive/sys/ drawer if they exist. So, if you like
these then copy them there (or just the ones you like).
@{par}
@{par}The NewIcons package can be found on Aminet: util/wb/NewIcons.lha

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Guides" "Guides (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "8"
@TOC "8"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}Guides (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The Guides drawer should contain the following icons:
@{par}@{code}
DC.guide.info      DCEditor.guide.info
DCGfx.guide.info   DCPrefs.guide.info
DCSfx.guide.info   PacMan.guide.info

@{body}This drawer also contains a @{b}MegaBall.guide icon@{ub} done by my little brother @{"Troy" LINK "Thanks"}
(14 years old). In my opinion, I think it is better than some of the other
icons I have seen uploaded to Aminet by people who ask for ShareWare fees!
@{par}
@{par}These icons follow the AmigaGuide standard icon developed by @{"Roman Patzner" LINK "Card"}.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "ID" "ImageDrawers (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "8"
@TOC "8"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}ImageDrawers (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The ImageDrawers drawer should contain the following icons:
@{par}
@{par}DiamondCaves.info   Deluxe_PacMan.info
@{par}MCP.info            Photogenics.info
@{par}
@{par}These are just some drawers I drew when the occasion arose; I know there are
not a whole lot, but @{"Roman Patzner" LINK "Card"} beats me to it @{b}@{apen 2}:@{ub}@{apen 1})

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Enlan" "Enlan (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "8"
@TOC "8"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}Enlan (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The Enlan drawer should contain the following icons:
@{par}
@{par}EID.info       IConfig.info
@{par}NetRexx.info   Start-DFS.info
@{par}

@ENDNODE


@NODE "16" "16_Color (dir)"
@NEXT "Require"
@PREV "Icons"
@TOC "Icons"

@{code}@{jcenter}@{apen 2}16_Color (dir)

@{jleft}@{apen 1}@{body}The 16_Color drawer should contain the following icons:
@{par}@{code}
Anime.info     Anime2.info
Anime3.info    Courtney.info
Kiki.info      Toaster.info

@{body}These 16 colour icons were created using the PictIcon program by Chad
Randall (Aminet:util/wb). With a 16 colour WB and the right tool it is really
easy to create nice looking icons!
@{par}
@{par}They follow the standard developed by @{"Roman Patzner" LINK "Card"} - 55x35 pixel, because it
is closer to a  3:4 ratio.
@{par}@{code}
@{apen 3}To install 16 colour palette on your system:@{apen 1}

  1. Change your screenmode to 16 colors.
  2. Load the User-Startup into your editor and change the MagicWB-Demon to:
     Run >NIL: C:MagicWB-Demon 4,123,123,123 5,175,175,175 6,170,144,124 7,255,169,151 8,0,0,255 9,50,50,50 10,96,128,96 11,226,209,119 12,255,212,203 13,122,96,72 14,210,210,210 15,229,93,93
     (This line is provided in the @{" S (dir) " LINK "S"} of this archive).
  3. Do the same with your Startup-Sequence
  4. Load Prefs/Palette and change the last four colours to
            255,212,203   122,96,72   210,210,210   229,93,93
     and save it. After re-boot everything should work fine.

  @{b}Note@{ub}: MUI applications look strange without rearranging the colors.

@{apen 3}To simply test this or see what it will look like:@{apen 1}

  1. Open the @{" P&C " LINK "P&C"} drawer of this archive.
  2. Click on @{b}ClickMeFirst@{ub}.
  3. Click on @{b}ClickForColors16@{ub}.
  4. Click on @{b}ClickForScreen@{ub} and slide the Colors slider to 16 and hit @{b}USE@{ub}.

  To get everything back to normal just follow steps 3 & 4 for 8 colors
  instead of 16.

@ENDNODE

@REMARK------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE "C" "C (dir)"
@PREV "Intro"
@TOC "Intro"

